info.description:
========
Compyler
========

Compyler is a Python compiler. It takes your Python source code and compiles it to C code using libpython, and then to
machine code. Unlike other compilers, like Nuitka, Compyler uses PEP 3107 and 526 type annotations to deduce types for
compilation. Unlike Cython, Compyler takes 100% pure Python code, and does not rely on custom type syntax to compile to
C code. Additionally, Compyler only supports Python 3.6+.

Status
======

Compyler is currently in the planning stages. There is an idea of how the project will work, but no released code (yet).
Code for Compyler will be released once a minimal subset of Python is supported. Development will be in the open on
Github.

Python Versions Supported
=========================

For several reasons, Python 3.6 will likely be selected as the minimum supported Python version. The main reason for
this decision is that type annotation syntax is not supported until Python 3.6.
